refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
stringfalsestristr stringhaystack stringneedle boolbefore_needle&false;
Returns all of haystack starting from and including the first occurrence of needle to the end.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Returns the matched substring. If needle is not
 found, returns &false;.

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;



    &strings.changelog.ascii-case-folding;
    &strings.changelog.needle-empty;


     8.0.0

      Passing an &integer; as needle is no longer supported.




     7.3.0

      Passing an &integer; as needle has been deprecated.

  &reftitle.examples;



    stristr example


<?php
  $email = 'USER@EXAMPLE.com';
  echo stristr($email, 'e'); // outputs ER@EXAMPLE.com
  echo stristr($email, 'e', true); // outputs US
?>







    Testing if a string is found or not


<?php
  $string = 'Hello World!';
  if(stristr($string, 'earth') === FALSE) {
    echo '"earth" not found in string';
  }
// outputs: "earth" not found in string
?>







    Using a non "string" needle


<?php
  $string = 'APPLE';
  echo stristr($string, 97); // 97 = lowercase a
// outputs: APPLE
?>
